9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 258, L.D. 404, “An Act Regarding the
10 Confidentiality of Certain Lottery Winner Identities”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 8 MRSA §378-B is enacted to read:
14 §378-B. Lottery winner identity; confidentiality
15 The identity of a person awarded a prize of $100,000 or more and the identity of a
16 person who is a participant in the Address Confidentiality Program under Title 5, section
17 90-B awarded a prize of any amount are confidential unless the person awarded such a
18 prize provides written authorization to the bureau allowing the disclosure of that person's
19 identity. The bureau may disclose the identity of the person to another state agency solely
20 for purposes authorized under state and federal law, and that state agency is prohibited from
21 further disclosing the person's identity.
22 Information designated as confidential under this section is not a public record as
23 defined in Title 1, section 402, subsection 3.'
24 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
25 number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
